information she said in an interview 
but were realizing more and more that if a good rapport isnt 
established with a client these programs are not going to work 
organizations around the world are beginning to recognize that 
this is a big problem she said so the moment is right to 
focus not only on what we say but how we say it 
health workers are being taught to treat clients as equals to 
ask questions that draw out more information to speak in native 
languages to use more respectful forms of address to let the 
client ask questions and many other approaches piotrow said 
to help in the effort johns hopkins in the past month has 
mailed out some 150000 copies of a special issue of its 
international journal population reports concentrating on 
counseling 
in addition special counseling seminars have been held in egypt 
and programs are being scheduled in such countries as ghana 
zimbabwe burkina faso mali zaire india brazil mexico and 
peru among others 
piotrows counseling program is getting under way even as the 
independent population reference bureau reports that world 
population is growing faster than expected 
current growth of 17 percent annually means the world could 
double its current 5 billion total in just 40 years the bureau 
reported anticipated declines in the growth rates in many less 
developed nations have not occurred as rapidly as hoped the bureau 
said 
at this stage better communication probably will make more 
difference now than any other single factor in these programs 
she said 
the federal agency for international development which supports 
her work places heavy emphasis on voluntary family planning 
programs and that requires good information for the participants 
she says 
in many ways its an effort related to the debate under way in 
the united states concentrating on what has come to be called 
patient rights to be informed and make their own medical 
decisions 
its a big challenge for people in public health because 
doctors have been used to giving orders heres a prescription 
you take it and youll get well piotrow said 
its a new era in health programs and its going to depend on 
individuals making informed choices themselves 
in the age of modern technology medical personnel learned 
how to use all the machines but somehow the interpersonal side got 
a little neglected she added 
once counselors understand better ways to deal with clients the 
same approaches can be used in aids counseling nutrition 
counseling and even drug counseling she added 
</TEXT>
