agreement signed in sapoa nicaragua march 23 the pact calls for 
contra forces to enter truce zones after which the government is 
to free 700 political prisoners and allow contras to join talks 
with nicaraguan political parties 
during the truce contra forces may receive humanitarian 
supplies but rebel leaders say the latest round of talks stalled 
over how that food clothing and medicine would be delivered 
the contras friday rejected a sandinista proposal that the 
international committee of the red cross resupply the rebels 
chamorro said red cross in nicaragua is just another arm of 
the sandinista government he preferred that a private carrier 
agreeable to both sides bring in the goods 
the rebels also turned down a government proposal to extend by a 
